review_blob:
Lively head, rich amber color
Toasty aroma,
Full-bodied malt flavor
Not too carbonated, slightly creamy and thick mouthfeel from all that malt.

Appearance is a semi-opaque brown with tan head
Served too cold to get much aroma, but some caramel, smoke, and a bit of yeast.
The smoke appears again in the taste, otherwise a bit salty/sweet.
Carbonation is too much, beer was much better after I let it sit and warm up and soften.
beer_name: Jing A Smoke On The Beech

review_blob:
Very pale, slightly cloudy appearance
Fresh orange zest aroma dominates
Taste is light, notes of wheat, oranges, and some sweetnes
Very dry finish and high carb, like champagne.
 Not bad, very refreshing, but Id prefer it with a bit more body and spice.

Golden and a good fluffy head.
Very floral aroma, different from what youd get in an ipa, and lacks the spicyness of a saison.
Hard to place the flavor, but its a slightly light saison with more some floral/honey notes.
Medium body, goes down very smoothly.
beer_name: Jing A Full Moon Farmhouse Ale

review_blob:
Pours golden/orange 
Great floral aroma from citra dry-hopping
Nice balance of sweetness and hop bitterness
Good carb and a typical ipa bitter finish
One of the best IPAs Ive had in a while. Like sculpin, but slightly less sharp.

Pours amber orange and clear, with a finger of head
Nice piney, even smokey chinook aroma
Medium bitterness on the malty backbone
The body is medum/light, a session beer. Good carbonation.
beer_name: Jing A Bittersweet Symphony Session IPA

review_blob:
Clear, pale with 1/2 inch head.
Fruity watermelon aroma. 
Not as sweet as expected, but could use more tartness.
Nice dry finish, definitely sessionable.
beer_name: Jing A Big Slice Watermelon Wheat
